   ->with(['project', 'assignedTo', 'createdBy', 'workOrderList', 'tasks'])\\n    ->orderBy('due_date')\\n    ->get()\\n```\\n\\n**Important:** The controller fetches ALL work orders without any archived status filtering at the page level. All statuses are included in the dataset passed to the frontend.\\n\\n### 3. WorkOrder Model & Archived Status\\n\\n**Model File:**\\n- `/app/Models/WorkOrder.php`\\n\\n**Archived Status Representation:**\\n- Uses an **enum-based status system** (not a boolean field)\\n- Status field is a string column with enum cast to `WorkOrderStatus` class\\n- Archived status is represented as `WorkOrderStatus::Archived` with value `'archived'`\\n\\n**Relevant Scopes in the Model:**\\n```php\\npublic function scopeArchived(Builder $query): Builder\\n{\\n    return $query->where('status', WorkOrderStatus::Archived);\\n}\\n\\npublic function scopeNotArchived(Builder $query): Builder\\n{\\n    return $query->where('status', '!=', WorkOrderStatus::Archived);\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Status Enum Definition:**\\n- `/app/Enums/WorkOrderStatus.php` - Defines all 9 statuses: Draft, Active, InReview, Approved, Delivered, Blocked, Cancelled, RevisionRequested, Archived\\n\\n### 4. Existing Filtering Logic for Archived Work Orders\\n\\n**At the Controller Level:**\\n- The general `getWorkOrders()` fetches ALL statuses\\n- But there are status-specific methods like:\\n  - `getMyWorkWorkOrders()` - Excludes `Delivered` and `Cancelled` (line 187)\\n  - No explicit archived filtering in main page data fetch\\n\\n**At the Frontend Level (React):**\\n- **Calendar View:** Shows ALL work orders without filtering archived status\\n- **Archive View:** Specifically shows ONLY projects with `archived` or `completed` status (line 27-29 of archive-view.tsx)\\n- **All Projects View:** Filters to show only `active` or `on_hold` projects (line 158)\\n\\n**In Work Order Type Definition:**\\n- `/resources/js/types/work.d.ts` - WorkOrder status includes: `'draft' | 'active' | 'in_review' | 'approved' | 'delivered' | 'archived'` (line 58)\\n\\n### 5. Database Schema\\n\\n**Migration:**\\n- `/database/migrations/2026_01_10_000003_create_work_orders_table.php`\\n- Uses soft deletes: `$table->softDeletes()` (line 29)\\n- Status stored as string field with default value `'draft'`\\n- Indexed on `['team_id', 'status']` for efficient queries\\n\\n### Key Insight:\\n\\nThe Calendar View currently **includes archived work orders** in its display because the controller's `getWorkOrders()` method doesn't filter them out. To exclude archived items from the calendar, you would need to apply either:\\n1. A `.notArchived()` scope in the controller query\\n2. Client-side filtering in the CalendarView component based on `wo.status !== 'archived'`\"}]"}}
